Package <Unnamed>

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Book
    The book class is responsible for creating the book object with the variables that consist of its serial number, name, published date, and if it is checked out.
    Date
    The date class helps with verifying that a given date is accurate (not too old and not an impossibly made up one).
    Kiosk
    The Kiosk class is for processing the command lines from the console and giving the required output back to the user.
    Library
    The library class consists of methods that are called within other methods and also methods that commit the action that matches the user's command.
    RunProject1
    The RunProject1 class is a driver class to run our Project1.The main method will call the run() method in the Kiosk class.
